#originalTopic=does-owning-a-gun-make-you-safer
How many handgun owners have murdered their own relatives in a fit or because of a paranoid mis-identification of a possible "intruder"?  These people were obviously pretty unstable to begin with - but they just passed through the filter and got a gun.  The number of these cases - compared with the actual use of handguns for legitimate self defense - looks pretty bad to me, which is why most police chiefs seem to take a dim view of gun-toting citizens.  I have to agree with that view, I regret to say 